16
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:01,680
<i>The men are spending</i>
<i>their days in training,</i>

17
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:04,610
<i>with the goal of defeating the Saiyans.</i>

18
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:07,320
<i>However, as for Gohan...</i>

19
00:02:19,230 --> 00:02:24,730
<i>"Run, Gohan! Longing for Mount</i>
<i>Paozu, Where Chichi is Waiting."</i>

20
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,860
Big Brother...

21
00:02:58,570 --> 00:03:00,470
Mm-hmm, this one's dead.

22
00:03:00,510 --> 00:03:01,640
Really?

23
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:04,470
You can tell if he's
dead or not by doing that?

24
00:03:04,510 --> 00:03:09,610
Of course you can! You're five already,
and you don't even know that?

25
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:14,020
I did so know!

26
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:16,890
It doesn't look like he's
carrying anything worth any money.

27
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,050
Big Brother, over there!

28
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:23,260
All right, we will reap something!

29
00:03:27,470 --> 00:03:29,530
Awesome!

30
00:03:36,650 --> 00:03:39,740
That's mine...

31
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:43,080
Did he die again?

32
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:46,050
He doesn't look injured, huh?

33
00:03:46,090 --> 00:03:47,580
You're right.

34
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:51,990
He's coming around.

35
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,360
–Um...
–I'm Rom. Nice to meet you.

36
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,930
I'm his sister, Chiko. Who are you?

37
00:03:58,970 --> 00:04:01,260
I'm Son Gohan.

38
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:02,800
–How old are you?
–Four.

39
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:06,600
Hooray! You're younger than me!

40
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:08,240
Where are we?

41
00:04:09,650 --> 00:04:12,040
This is our cottage.

42
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:15,840
Not bad, huh?
Where did you come from?

43
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:19,410
I don't know. I think it
was a desert somewhere.

44
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:27,620
Well, no matter. In any case,
as of today, you're one of us.

45
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:30,560
It might be rough, but
don't cry, the way Chiko does.

46
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:33,060
"Mom! Where have you gone?!"

47
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:35,000
I don't cry anymore!

48
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,600
Um, I...

49
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:40,600
Listen, from now on,
you have to call me Big Sister.

50
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,840
There's no need to be shy.

51
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:45,780
Without any parents,
we all have to help each other.

52
00:04:46,850 --> 00:04:50,510
What's the matter? If you want
to tell us something, speak up.

53
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:54,620
I'm sorry. It's been a long
time since I talked to anyone.

54
00:04:54,660 --> 00:04:56,560
I can't speak that well.

55
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:24,610
About two years ago,
there was this gigantic tsunami.

56
00:05:24,650 --> 00:05:27,680
It swallowed up the whole city!

57
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:31,690
It was scary!

58
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:37,490
This place is packed with
kids like us that don't have homes.

59
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:53,670
Um, but I...

60
00:05:56,620 --> 00:05:59,350
Uh-oh, they're making their regular stop.

61
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:01,020
Regular stop?

62
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:03,550
Uh-huh! Hurry!

63
00:06:16,070 --> 00:06:18,060
Hurry! They'll catch you!

64
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:36,080
Wait here. Once I take
Chiko across, I'll be right back for you.

65
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:05,520
Come on...

66
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:35,010
Take that! You guys can't catch us!

67
00:07:35,050 --> 00:07:36,450
Dammit!

68
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:42,620
They make sure to come here once every day.

69
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:43,820
Who are they?

70
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:45,150
The guys from the institution.

71
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:48,820
They're trying to catch
us and toss us in the pokey.

72
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:50,190
Is that a scary place?

73
00:07:50,230 --> 00:07:52,830
According to the folks
who escaped from there,

74
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:56,970
they were picked on every day,
and got smacked with slippers.

75
00:07:57,010 --> 00:08:01,140
You can't come out of there for
the rest of your life, that's for sure.

76
00:08:01,810 --> 00:08:04,540
On top of that, they
cut your nails every night!

77
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:07,780
Let go of me! No! Oww!

78
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:12,150
Stop it! You're hurting me, I tell you!

79
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:22,820
Piegero!

80
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:26,630
She doesn't want to go. Cut it out!

81
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:30,660
You again?! Come on, now!

82
00:08:45,690 --> 00:08:47,210
Why, you–!

83
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:05,270
Stop that!

84
00:09:08,310 --> 00:09:11,540
You children up in the tree, come on down here!

85
00:09:11,580 --> 00:09:16,280
If you do, you'll get new clothes,
a clean room, and a hot meal!

86
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,050
Really?

87
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:18,910
Dummy! Don't be fooled!

88
00:09:18,950 --> 00:09:21,450
We don't want any of that! Get out of here!

89
00:09:21,490 --> 00:09:26,190
So then, do you plan to go on
living in a place like this forever?

90
00:09:26,230 --> 00:09:28,860
You think we're about to
put ourselves in your care?!

91
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:31,590
We'll go on living by ourselves just fine!

92
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:36,430
Yeah! Yeah! Get out
of here! Get out of here!

93
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:39,130
Get out of here!
Get out of here!

94
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,610
Yay! And don't come back!

95
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:52,550
We have a new kid?

96
00:09:52,590 --> 00:09:55,320
Apparently, he got shipwrecked
out at sea, and washed up here.

97
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:57,320
I'm Son Gohan. Nice to meet you.

98
00:09:57,360 --> 00:10:01,560
Hey, this boy is still little, so
give him a comparable share of food.

99
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:04,390
Look who's talking.
The same goes for you, doesn't it?

100
00:10:04,430 --> 00:10:05,760
I guess so.

101
