Well, anyhow, as a fellow person
without any family, let's stick together.

102
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:11,230
Come on over,
come on over! Delicious stuff!

103
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:13,860
Welcome by, son.
I'll let you have them cheap.

104
00:11:22,110 --> 00:11:23,240
Yow!

105
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:24,670
Yow-ow-ow-ow!

106
00:11:24,710 --> 00:11:26,070
What's the matter, son?

107
00:11:26,110 --> 00:11:29,240
It hurts! It hurts! It hurts!

108
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,250
–All right, now!
–Okay.

109
00:11:31,290 --> 00:11:33,080
It hurts! It hurts!

110
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,080
What's the matter?

111
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:38,050
It hurts! It hurts!

112
00:11:38,090 --> 00:11:39,050
It hurts!

113
00:11:39,090 --> 00:11:41,620
Where does it hurt?

114
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,220
It hurts!

115
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:46,630
It hurts! It hurts! It hurts!
It hurts! It hurts! It hurts!

116
00:11:46,670 --> 00:11:48,230
So, it's you guys! Hold it!

117
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,230
It hurts!

118
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:51,240
You bastards!

119
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:53,670
Hold it!

120
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,580
You hold it!

121
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:02,410
Dammit!

122
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:05,590
Thieves!

123
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,490
Hey, you!

124
00:12:22,770 --> 00:12:24,300
Hold it!

125
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:55,240
Take that!

126
00:12:56,140 --> 00:12:58,270
Why, you–! Hey!

127
00:12:58,310 --> 00:13:00,270
See? That was pretty fun, wasn't it?

128
00:13:00,310 --> 00:13:01,640
Uh-huh!

129
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,940
Even without parents, children still grow up!

130
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:04,940
Yeah, yeah!

131
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:08,140
Well said! We're growing up fine, huh?

132
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:08,980
What's the matter?

133
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:11,320
Hmm? Nothing.

134
00:14:19,390 --> 00:14:21,350
What's the matter? Need to pee?

135
00:14:21,390 --> 00:14:23,050
What are you doing?

136
00:14:23,090 --> 00:14:26,720
Standing watch. We've been
causing trouble all over, after all.

137
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:30,230
Sometimes there are people
that come after us at night here.

138
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:32,290
What is it, if you didn't
come out here to pee?

139
00:14:36,770 --> 00:14:43,300
I'm not an orphan. I have a mother,
and I was actually on my way home to her.

140
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:46,580
Oh, so the little boy has a home, huh?

141
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:53,250
I'm sorry, I just couldn't say anything.

142
00:14:53,290 --> 00:14:55,080
There's nothing you have to apologize for.

143
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:58,090
I guess I jumped to the wrong conclusion.

144
00:14:58,130 --> 00:14:59,750
Where is your home?

145
00:14:59,790 --> 00:15:02,160
In a bamboo grove on Mount Paozu.

146
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,760
Mount Paozu? That's pretty far, huh?

147
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,330
–You know it?
–Yeah.

148
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:08,930
Please tell me the way, if you would!

149
00:15:08,970 --> 00:15:11,930
